    "verdict": "ok",
    "note": "Going to for evidence-based predictions (be + going to + base) vs will (opinion / spontaneous decision); plans; is/are agreement; 3 error classes (missing be / base-after-going-to / agreement). 37 vocab + 28 grammar, full v1 parity (floor 22 → 28 items / 10 formats / diff 1-3). 4 verify lenses clean after fixes: reworded 7 multiword travel-phrase defs off their headword tokens; granted the going-to/will spine (going/will/won't/'ll + contraction fragments) + inflections + def carriers; stripped 9 cross-item-redundant glosses; changed tf evidence 'edge'→'end' (untaught, inside a lang:de prompt the gate doesn't level-scope); completed the tr.001 answer grid; disambiguated a sentence-initial 'Sie'→'Das Mädchen'; reworded 'Verneinung'→functional 'das Gegenteil (mit not)'. Editorial call: KEPT 'Vorhersage'/'Beweis' (prediction/evidence) in prompts — these name the communicative FUNCTION (predicting from visible evidence), not a grammar form like 'Passiv', so they are content not meta-talk (precedent: approved g3-u10 'über die Zukunft'). Defensible non-issues: 'could'/'diamonds' level-gloss warns are gate-taught (validate green); the 2 'find out' g-values are rule-compliant (g = one bank de value; full meaning carried in enToDe). 39 translation audits accurate both directions. Validate fully green (0 errors, 0 warns)."
